From 20965809f4bebd76e112f38c473f75f620d6b2f2 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: prcdslnc13 <prcdslnc13@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 27 Apr 2026 16:54:12 -0500
Subject: [PATCH] Switch MCP stdio transport from LSP framing to NDJSON
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

claw's MCP stdio transport sent and expected LSP-style
`Content-Length: N\r\n\r\n<json>` framing on both the client side
(`mcp_stdio.rs`) and the `claw mcp serve` server side (`mcp_server.rs`).
The MCP stdio spec is newline-delimited JSON: one JSON message per line,
no headers. The Python `mcp` SDK (which most off-the-shelf MCP servers
use, including the user's `brain` server) only implements NDJSON, so
claw could not communicate with any standard-SDK-built MCP server in
either direction.

Symptom from the user's session 2026-04-27: with brain MCP wired through
`~/.claw/settings.json`, claw spawned the server, which then flooded
stderr with `pydantic.ValidationError: Invalid JSON: ... input_value=
'Content-Length: 156\n'` because brain tried to JSON-parse claw's
header line.

Fix is symmetric on both ends:

- `mcp_stdio.rs::write_jsonrpc_message` now serializes to a string and
  writes `<json>\n` via the existing `write_line` helper.
- `mcp_stdio.rs::read_jsonrpc_message` reads a line, trims, and parses
  with `serde_json::from_str`. Blank lines are skipped to tolerate
  defensive padding from peers.
- `write_frame`, `read_frame`, and `encode_frame` are removed (no
  remaining users).
- `mcp_server.rs::run` uses a new `read_message` helper that returns
  one trimmed line per call (None on EOF). `write_response` writes
  `<json>\n`.
- Module doc updated to reflect NDJSON, not LSP-framed.

Test fixtures and unit tests:

- All four Python server fixtures (`jsonrpc-mcp.py`, `fake-mcp-server.py`,
  `manager-mcp-server.py`, `initialize-disconnect.py`) plus the bridge
  fixture in `mcp_tool_bridge.rs` and the CLI fixture in
  `rusty-claude-cli/src/main.rs` now read with `sys.stdin.readline()`
  + `json.loads(line)` and write with `sys.stdout.write(json.dumps(...) + '\n')`.
- The `INVALID_TOOL_CALL_RESPONSE` mode in `fake-mcp-server.py` now
  writes a single `nope!\n` line instead of a Content-Length-framed
  payload. The `manager_surfaces_parse_errors_from_tool_calls` test's
  serde_json error-message assertion still matches.
- `write_jsonrpc_request_emits_content_length_frame` renamed to
  `write_jsonrpc_request_roundtrips_over_ndjson`.
- `given_lowercase_content_length_when_initialize_then_response_parses`
  deleted — the test exercised LSP header case-insensitivity, which
  has no NDJSON analogue. The corresponding `MCP_LOWERCASE_CONTENT_LENGTH`
  env support in the fixture is also removed.

Verification (from `rust/`):

- `cargo build --workspace` clean.
- `cargo test --workspace`: all 936 tests pass; only failure is the
  pre-existing `resumed_status_command_emits_structured_json_when_requested`
  test, which also fails on `main` and is unrelated to this patch.
- `cargo clippy --workspace --all-targets -- -D warnings` clean.

Note: this is a fork-side fix per the personal-build hardening pattern
(`fork-is-personal-hardened-build-not-upstream-contribution`). Upstream
may have its own opinions about backward compatibility with LSP-style
servers, so this is not contributed back to `ultraworkers/claw-code`.
